value.0: Prepare to die, fool!
So, little worm, do you have any last words before joining this witch in death?!

That is a matter which does not concern you, little fool, and one which I am quite afraid you will not live long enough to learn... Now, prepare to meet the Mother of Death, and accept her cold embrace!

<StartAction>[Ghasaran cackles evilly.]</Start> True, but you are also no longer of use to me either... Do not worry, though. Your soul shall pass to the Mother of Death, and such a sacrifice will please her greatly...
Now, prepare to die, fool!
<StartAction>[Ghasaran lowers his mace, and prepares to engage you in combat... His men jump eagerly into the fray...]</Start>
<StartAction>[Ghasaran nods approvingly in your direction.]</Start> So we have the daughter of Dy'nesh in our grasp! The Dark Mother will be pleased...
You have done well, <Race> <man/woman>, in leading us to the Elven witch... but I am afraid your usefulness has come to an end...
Oh, but I do believe it is you that are mistaken, little fool! Soon, you shall feel the fury of the Mother of Death unleashed upon you, and accept her dark embrace...
Little fool! I must do nothing, particular not at the command of a pitiful <man/woman> such as you!
<StartAction>[Ghasaran snickers at you.]</Start> Yes, it seems that I am...
Men! Secure the doors! Let us spill the blood of these fools for the glory of the Mother of Death!
<StartAction>[Suddenly, Ghasaran's men swing the doors to the chamber shut, quickly barring them and securing the lock. It appears you are trapped in here along with Kara...]</Start>

<StartAction>[The terrifying visage of the man called Ghasaran looks down upon you.]</Start> So, you have returned, <Race> <man/woman>, and I hope you have reconsidered telling us where we may find the witch we seek!
<StartAction>[Before you stands a man adorned in blood red armor, his face concealed behind a hideous mask. Just the mere sight of him is enough to send shivers running down your spine...]</Start>
<StartAction>[The fearsome man points at you.]</Start> You there! <Race> <man/woman>! I must speak with you!
<StartAction>[The man grabs you roughly by the arm.]</Start> You will hear me out, <Race> <man/woman>, for such is my demand, and none refuse me!
<StartAction>[You hear a deep snarl from within the depths of the man's helm.]</Start> You would be wise to listen to my words, <Race> <man/woman>, for you may be rewarded well for your aid!

<StartAction>[The man appears on the brink of lashing out at you, but after a long moment, he finally backs away.]</Start> Go then! Return to me should you desire the opportunity to be well rewarded with a purse of 500 gold pieces!
I am Ghasaran, and I seek your aid! I have heard word that you witnessed the summoning of a spirit of the Underworld in this city, and I desire to know where I may find the witch who called it forth!
Tell me of her whereabouts, and you shall be rewarded well with a purse of 500 gold pieces!
<StartAction>[Ghasaran growls at you menacingly.]</Start> So be it, <Race> <man/woman>! We shall simply have to find the witch on our own! Do not worry... She will not escape our grasp for long!
<StartAction>[Ghasaran motions for his lackeys to accompany him, and they quickly depart...]</Start>

<StartAction>[Ghasaran looks down upon you, as though searching your mind for the truth of your answer.]</Start> So be it! We must go in search of the witch at once, before she has a chance to escape our clutches!
For now, I shall give you half of your promised reward... To claim the other half, I must insist you come to the witch's location, and ensure that we procure her with no difficulty...

<StartAction>[An unearthly growl rumbles inside Ghasaran's mask.]</Start> You shall demand nothing of me! Either accept my terms or refuse them, but I shall pay you no more until the witch is in our custody!
<StartAction>[You can feel Ghasaran's icy stare bearing down into you.]</Start> You will accept it, or receive no reward, fool! I must ensure that you are telling the truth, now mustn't I?
Come join us in abducting the witch, and when the deed is done, you shall be paid in full... <StartAction>[Apparently considering the matter resolved, Ghasaran turns away from you.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Ghasaran motions for his lackeys to accompany him, and they quickly depart in the direction you pointed them...]</Start>
<StartAction>[Ghasaran looks down upon you, as though searching your mind for the truth of your answer.]</Start> So be it! We shall go at once to find the witch at this tavern!
For now, I shall give you half of your promised reward... To claim the other half, I must insist you come to the witch's location, and ensure that we procure her with no difficulty...

<StartAction>[An unearthly growl rumbles inside Ghasaran's mask.]</Start> You shall demand nothing of me! Either accept my terms or refuse them, but I shall pay you no more until the witch is in our custody!
<StartAction>[You can feel Ghasaran's icy stare bearing down into you.]</Start> You will accept it, or receive no reward, fool! I must ensure that you are telling the truth, now mustn't I?
Come join us in abducting the witch, and when the deed is done, you shall be paid in full... <StartAction>[Apparently considering the matter resolved, Ghasaran turns away from you.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Ghasaran motions for his lackeys to accompany him, and they quickly depart in the direction you pointed them...]</Start>
That is for us to know only! It is of no concern to you! If you wish to receive your reward, you will cooperate with us fully!
<StartAction>[Ghasaran shakes visibly in anger.]</Start> If you must know, the woman we seek is a traitor to our holiest of orders, and we seek to bring vengeance upon her!
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_PREL_KARA_2" >>

Why do you want Kara so badly?
Why do you wish me dead?
You won't take me without a fight! <StartAction>[Launch into an attack against Ghasaran and his men.]</Start>
You are making a foolish mistake if you think you can cross me!
I demand you pay me the remaining gold you promised, and allow me to leave in peace!
What's this? You're going to betray me?!
Excuse me, but I do not have time for this nonsense right now...
Well there's a first time for everything! Now move out of my way!
I told you once to move out of my way... I shall not repeat it again!
<StartAction>[Leave the presence of this strange man as quickly as you can.]</Start>
That's quite a reward... Perhaps we should talk this out a bit further...
I'm sorry, but do I know you?
Who are you? What do you want from me?
Give me some time to think about it, and perhaps I'll take you up on your offer...
I am sorry, but I must refuse your request. I simply do not trust the look of you...
<StartAction>[Lie.]</Start> I believe I saw the woman you seek heading towards the docks... You might be able to find her there...
I demand you give me all the payment at this moment!
That was never part of our agreement!
Very well. I shall meet you there...
<StartAction>[Truth.]</Start> The woman you seek, an Elven maiden by the name of Kara Dy'nesh, is staying at the Ravenclaw Tavern...
I demand you give me all the payment at this moment!
That was never part of our agreement!
Very well. I shall meet you there...
Why do you want to find this woman so badly?
No... First you tell me why you want her, then I'll decide whether to help you or not...
That's fair enough...
